==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Terrorism
<hw>Ter"ror*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>terrorisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of terrorizing,
or state of being terrorized; a mode of government by terror or
intimidation.</def> <rj><au>Jefferson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The practise of coercing governments to accede to
political demands by committing violence on civilian targets; any
similar use of violence to achieve goals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Terrorist</ent>⟦br⟧
